The paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks, for the classification of Alzheimer's disease from structural MRI data. This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves analyzing and interpreting medical images. Additionally, the use of deep learning algorithms for classification makes it likely to also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as these are all related fields that often overlap with computer vision.
